article.headline: Ball St. 79, Buffalo 73
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Skip Mills scored 20 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Ball State to a 79-73 victory over Buffalo on Wednesday. D'Andre Peyton came off the bench to add 18 points on 6-of-11 shooting for the Cardinals (8-15, 4-6, Mid-American Conference). Yassin Idbihi finished with 13 points and 14 rebounds and Andy Robinson added 13 points to lead the Bulls (10-13, 2-8) in their seventh straight road loss. Buffalo went on a 12-2 run over the first 4:56, but Peyton Stovall hit a 3-pointer with 6:49 left in the first half to cap a 24-6 Ball State run. The Cardinals never trailed in the second half. Buffalo committed 20 turnovers which the Cardinals turned into 25 points.
